theorem
(for x,y being (FinSequence of ( REAL )) holds (for M being (Matrix of ( REAL )) holds (((( len x ) = ( len M ) & ( len y ) = ( width M )) & ( len y ) > ( 0 )) implies ( ( QuadraticForm (x,M,y) ) @ ) = ( QuadraticForm (y,( M @ ),x) ))))
proof
let x being (FinSequence of ( REAL ));
let y being (FinSequence of ( REAL ));
let M being (Matrix of ( REAL ));
assume that
A1: ( len x ) = ( len M )
and
A2: ( len y ) = ( width M )
and
A3: ( len y ) > ( 0 );
A4: ( len ( M @ ) ) = ( len y ) by A2,MATRIX_1:def 6;
A5: ( width ( M @ ) ) = ( len x ) by A1,A2,A3,MATRIX_2:10;
then A6: (( len ( QuadraticForm (y,( M @ ),x) ) ) = ( len y ) & ( width ( QuadraticForm (y,( M @ ),x) ) ) = ( len x )) by A4,CKB53:def 1;
A7: ( len ( ( QuadraticForm (x,M,y) ) @ ) ) = ( width ( QuadraticForm (x,M,y) ) ) by MATRIX_1:def 6;
A8: ( width ( QuadraticForm (x,M,y) ) ) = ( len y ) by A1,A2,CKB53:def 1;
then A9: ( width ( ( QuadraticForm (x,M,y) ) @ ) ) = ( len ( QuadraticForm (x,M,y) ) ) by A3,MATRIX_2:10;
A10: (for i,j being Nat holds ([ i,j ] in ( Indices ( ( QuadraticForm (x,M,y) ) @ ) ) implies ( ( QuadraticForm (y,( M @ ),x) ) * (i,j) ) = ( ( ( QuadraticForm (x,M,y) ) @ ) * (i,j) )))
proof
let i being Nat;
let j being Nat;
assume A11: [ i,j ] in ( Indices ( ( QuadraticForm (x,M,y) ) @ ) );
reconsider i,j as (Element of ( NAT )) by ORDINAL1:def 12;
A12: 1 <= j by A11,MATRIXC1:1;
A13: j <= ( len ( QuadraticForm (x,M,y) ) ) by A9,A11,MATRIXC1:1;
then A14: j <= ( len M ) by A1,A2,CKB53:def 1;
A15: 1 <= i by A11,MATRIXC1:1;
A16: i <= ( width ( QuadraticForm (x,M,y) ) ) by A7,A11,MATRIXC1:1;
then i <= ( width M ) by A1,A2,CKB53:def 1;
then A17: [ j,i ] in ( Indices M ) by A12,A15,A14,MATRIXC1:1;
A18: j <= ( width ( M @ ) ) by A1,A2,A5,A13,CKB53:def 1;
A19: 1 <= i by A11,MATRIXC1:1;
1 <= i by A11,MATRIXC1:1;
then A20: [ j,i ] in ( Indices ( QuadraticForm (x,M,y) ) ) by A16,A12,A13,MATRIXC1:1;
i <= ( len ( M @ ) ) by A1,A2,A4,A16,CKB53:def 1;
then [ i,j ] in ( Indices ( M @ ) ) by A12,A19,A18,MATRIXC1:1;
then ( ( QuadraticForm (y,( M @ ),x) ) * (i,j) ) = ( ( ( y . i ) * ( ( M @ ) * (i,j) ) ) * ( x . j ) ) by A4,A5,CKB53:def 1
.= ( ( ( y . i ) * ( M * (j,i) ) ) * ( x . j ) ) by A17,MATRIX_1:def 6
.= ( ( ( x . j ) * ( M * (j,i) ) ) * ( y . i ) )
.= ( ( QuadraticForm (x,M,y) ) * (j,i) ) by A1,A2,A17,CKB53:def 1
.= ( ( ( QuadraticForm (x,M,y) ) @ ) * (i,j) ) by A20,MATRIX_1:def 6;
hence thesis;
end;
A21: ( len ( ( QuadraticForm (x,M,y) ) @ ) ) = ( width ( QuadraticForm (x,M,y) ) ) by MATRIX_1:def 6
.= ( len y ) by A1,A2,CKB53:def 1;
( width ( ( QuadraticForm (x,M,y) ) @ ) ) = ( len ( QuadraticForm (x,M,y) ) ) by A3,A8,MATRIX_2:10
.= ( len x ) by A1,A2,CKB53:def 1;
hence thesis by A21,A6,A10,MATRIX_1:21;
end;
